com.vmware.vapi.saml

Interface XmlPresentable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    SamlToken, ValidatableSamlToken, ValidatableSamlTokenEx

    public interface XmlPresentable
    Indicates that an object that can be presented as XML

    The schema of the XML representation is up to implementation.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Node importTo(Document hostDocument)
      Creates a copy of the XML representation of the object, imported into the given document.
      String toXml() 

    • Method Detail

      • toXml

        String toXml()
        Returns:
        object presented as a valid XML document string, not null

        The XML document will not have a <?xml declaration.

      • importTo

        Node importTo(Document hostDocument)
        Creates a copy of the XML representation of the object, imported into the given document.

        This method allows the implementations to restore XML metadata which is lost when a node is imported in other document or serialized to string.

        Parameters:
        hostDocument - required
        Returns:
        the cloned node, owned by the given document, not null
